<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PrimarySourceReference/995> rdfs:label "Primary Source Reference: #995" ;
	a dprr:PrimarySourceReference ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Diod. XXXIV/XXXV 5. [ erg. V. Herwerden]" ;
	dprr:forAssertion <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/976> .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/679> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #679" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Appointed to deal with a serious debt situation. This they did by payments from public funds, or by authorizing bankruptcy proceedings or surrender of property (Liv. 7.21.5-8; Gaius Inst. 4.23; cf. Rotondi 224; Frank, ESAR 1.29f.). On Publilius, see Lübker no. 2." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/678> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #678" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "Among the Vviri the identification of Papirius, Publilius, and Aemilius can only be tentative. On their names, see Fast. Cap. for 330, Act. Tr. for 339, and sources under 339, Consuls. In Livy Aemilius has the praenomen T. not otherwise known in the Gens Aemilia, while Ti. was frequent during this period." .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertion/976> rdfs:label "Post Assertion: #976" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertion ;
	dprr:isAboutPerson <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/Person/516> ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySource <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/1> ;
	dprr:hasPostAssertionNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/679> , <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/678> ;
	dprr:hasOriginalText "M. Papirius Pat. (22, cf. 48)" ;
	dprr:hasOffice <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/Office/46> ;
